## Section 13: Toast/Notification Component

### 13.1 Component Overview

**Description**: Temporary notification system with 4 semantic types (success, error, warning, info). Auto-dismisses after duration, positioned fixed top-right.

**Location**: `src/components/ui/Toast.tsx`

**When to Use**:
- ✅ Action feedback (save, delete, update)
- ✅ Error messages (API failures, validation errors)
- ✅ Success confirmations (payment complete, KYC approved)
- ✅ Warning alerts (session timeout, unsaved changes)
- ✅ Information messages (new feature announcements)

---

### 13.2 TypeScript Interface

```typescript
interface ToastProps {
  /** Unique identifier for toast management */
  id: string;

  /** Visual and semantic type */
  type: 'success' | 'error' | 'warning' | 'info';

  /** Primary message (bold) */
  title: string;

  /** Optional secondary message */
  message?: string;

  /** Auto-dismiss duration in milliseconds (default: 5000) */
  duration?: number;

  /** Callback when toast is closed */
  onClose: (id: string) => void;
}

// Toast Manager API
class ToastManager {
  show(toast: Omit<ToastProps, 'id' | 'onClose'>): void;
  remove(id: string): void;
  clear(): void;
}
```

---

### 13.3 All Toast Types

#### Success Toast
```tsx
toast.show({
  type: 'success',
  title: 'Payment Successful',
  message: 'Transaction ID: TXN123456',
  duration: 5000
});

// Visual Style:
// - Icon: CheckCircle (green)
// - Background: bg-green-50
// - Border: border-l-4 border-green-200
// - Text: text-green-800
```

#### Error Toast
```tsx
toast.show({
  type: 'error',
  title: 'Payment Failed',
  message: 'Insufficient balance. Please try again.',
  duration: 7000 // Longer for errors
});

// Visual Style:
// - Icon: XCircle (red)
// - Background: bg-red-50
// - Border: border-l-4 border-red-200
// - Text: text-red-800
```

#### Warning Toast
```tsx
toast.show({
  type: 'warning',
  title: 'Session Expiring Soon',
  message: 'Your session will expire in 5 minutes.',
  duration: 6000
});

// Visual Style:
// - Icon: AlertTriangle (yellow)
// - Background: bg-yellow-50
// - Border: border-l-4 border-yellow-200
// - Text: text-yellow-800
```

#### Info Toast
```tsx
toast.show({
  type: 'info',
  title: 'New Feature Available',
  message: 'Check out our new Smart Routing feature!',
  duration: 5000
});

// Visual Style:
// - Icon: Info (blue)
// - Background: bg-blue-50
// - Border: border-l-4 border-blue-200
// - Text: text-blue-800
```

---

### 13.4 Usage Pattern

#### Basic Usage
```tsx
import { toast } from '@/components/ui/Toast';

// In your component or function
const handleSave = async () => {
  try {
    await saveData();

    // Show success toast
    toast.show({
      type: 'success',
      title: 'Saved Successfully',
      message: 'Your changes have been saved.',
    });
  } catch (error) {
    // Show error toast
    toast.show({
      type: 'error',
      title: 'Save Failed',
      message: error.message,
      duration: 7000, // Longer duration for errors
    });
  }
};
```

---

### 13.5 Code Examples

#### Example 1: Payment Success
```tsx
const handlePayment = async (amount: number) => {
  try {
    const response = await processPayment(amount);

    toast.show({
      type: 'success',
      title: 'Payment Successful',
      message: `₹${amount.toLocaleString('en-IN')} processed. TXN ID: ${response.transactionId}`,
      duration: 6000,
    });

    navigate('/payment-success');
  } catch (error) {
    toast.show({
      type: 'error',
      title: 'Payment Failed',
      message: 'There was an error processing your payment. Please try again.',
      duration: 7000,
    });
  }
};
```

---

#### Example 2: Form Validation
```tsx
const handleSubmit = (data: FormData) => {
  // Validation
  if (!data.email) {
    toast.show({
      type: 'warning',
      title: 'Missing Email',
      message: 'Please enter your email address.',
    });
    return;
  }

  if (!isValidEmail(data.email)) {
    toast.show({
      type: 'error',
      title: 'Invalid Email',
      message: 'Please enter a valid email address.',
    });
    return;
  }

  // Submit success
  toast.show({
    type: 'success',
    title: 'Form Submitted',
    message: 'We will review your application shortly.',
  });
};
```

---

#### Example 3: KYC Status Update
```tsx
const checkKYCStatus = async () => {
  const status = await fetchKYCStatus();

  const messages = {
    approved: {
      type: 'success' as const,
      title: 'KYC Approved',
      message: 'Your account has been verified successfully.',
    },
    rejected: {
      type: 'error' as const,
      title: 'KYC Rejected',
      message: 'Please re-upload your documents with correct information.',
    },
    pending: {
      type: 'info' as const,
      title: 'KYC Under Review',
      message: 'We are reviewing your documents. This may take 24-48 hours.',
    },
  };

  toast.show(messages[status]);
};
```

---

#### Example 4: Session Management
```tsx
// Session timeout warning
useEffect(() => {
  const warningTime = sessionExpiry - 5 * 60 * 1000; // 5 minutes before

  const timer = setTimeout(() => {
    toast.show({
      type: 'warning',
      title: 'Session Expiring Soon',
      message: 'Your session will expire in 5 minutes. Please save your work.',
      duration: 10000, // Stay longer
    });
  }, warningTime);

  return () => clearTimeout(timer);
}, [sessionExpiry]);

// Session expired
const handleSessionExpired = () => {
  toast.show({
    type: 'error',
    title: 'Session Expired',
    message: 'Please log in again to continue.',
    duration: 0, // Stay until manually closed
  });

  navigate('/login');
};
```

---

#### Example 5: API Error Handling
```tsx
const apiErrorHandler = (error: AxiosError) => {
  const statusMessages = {
    400: {
      title: 'Invalid Request',
      message: 'Please check your input and try again.',
    },
    401: {
      title: 'Unauthorized',
      message: 'Your session has expired. Please log in again.',
    },
    403: {
      title: 'Access Denied',
      message: 'You do not have permission to perform this action.',
    },
    404: {
      title: 'Not Found',
      message: 'The requested resource was not found.',
    },
    500: {
      title: 'Server Error',
      message: 'Something went wrong. Please try again later.',
    },
  };

  const message = statusMessages[error.response?.status] || {
    title: 'Error',
    message: 'An unexpected error occurred.',
  };

  toast.show({
    type: 'error',
    ...message,
    duration: 7000,
  });
};
```

---

### 13.6 Toast Manager Pattern

#### Singleton Implementation
```typescript
// Toast manager is a singleton
class ToastManager {
  private toasts: Map<string, ToastProps> = new Map();
  private container: HTMLElement | null = null;
  private root: any = null;

  // Ensures container exists (creates on first use)
  private ensureContainer() {
    if (!this.container) {
      this.container = document.createElement('div');
      this.container.className = 'fixed top-4 right-4 z-50 space-y-2';
      document.body.appendChild(this.container);
      this.root = createRoot(this.container);
    }
  }

  // Renders all active toasts
  private render() {
    if (!this.root) return;

    const toastElements = Array.from(this.toasts.values()).map(toast => (
      <Toast key={toast.id} {...toast} onClose={this.remove.bind(this)} />
    ));

    this.root.render(<>{toastElements}</>);
  }

  // Public API: Show toast
  show(toast: Omit<ToastProps, 'id' | 'onClose'>) {
    const id = Math.random().toString(36).substr(2, 9);
    this.ensureContainer();
    this.toasts.set(id, { ...toast, id, onClose: this.remove.bind(this) });
    this.render();
  }

  // Public API: Remove specific toast
  remove(id: string) {
    this.toasts.delete(id);
    this.render();
  }

  // Public API: Clear all toasts
  clear() {
    this.toasts.clear();
    this.render();
  }
}

// Export singleton instance
export const toast = new ToastManager();
```

#### Usage Anywhere in App
```tsx
// No provider needed - use directly
import { toast } from '@/components/ui/Toast';

toast.show({ type: 'success', title: 'Done!' });
```

---

### 13.7 Auto-Dismiss Behavior

#### Default Duration
```tsx
// Default: 5000ms (5 seconds)
toast.show({
  type: 'success',
  title: 'Saved',
  // duration defaults to 5000
});
```

#### Custom Duration
```tsx
// Short duration (3 seconds)
toast.show({
  type: 'info',
  title: 'Copied to clipboard',
  duration: 3000,
});

// Long duration (10 seconds)
toast.show({
  type: 'warning',
  title: 'Important Notice',
  message: 'Please read this carefully.',
  duration: 10000,
});

// Never auto-dismiss (duration: 0 or Infinity)
toast.show({
  type: 'error',
  title: 'Critical Error',
  message: 'Manual action required.',
  duration: 0, // User must close manually
});
```

#### Recommended Durations
- **Success**: 5000ms (5s) - User quickly sees confirmation
- **Error**: 7000ms (7s) - User needs time to read error
- **Warning**: 6000ms (6s) - Important but not critical
- **Info**: 5000ms (5s) - Standard information
- **Critical**: 0ms (manual) - Requires user action

---

### 13.8 Positioning & Stacking

#### Fixed Position
```css
/* Toast container */
fixed top-4 right-4 z-50 space-y-2

/* Positioning */
- top-4: 1rem from top
- right-4: 1rem from right
- z-50: Above most content
- space-y-2: 0.5rem gap between toasts
```

#### Stacking Behavior
- New toasts appear at the **top** of the stack
- Old toasts stack below new toasts
- Each toast animates in with `slide-in-from-top-full`
- When dismissed, toast fades out and others shift up

#### Responsive Positioning
```tsx
// Mobile: Full width at top
<div className="fixed top-4 left-4 right-4 z-50 space-y-2 md:left-auto md:w-96">
  {/* Toasts */}
</div>
```

---

### 13.9 Animation & Transitions

#### Entry Animation
```tsx
className="animate-in slide-in-from-top-full duration-300"

// Keyframes (from tailwind.config.js)
'slide-in-top': {
  '0%': { transform: 'translateY(-100%)', opacity: '0' },
  '100%': { transform: 'translateY(0)', opacity: '1' },
}
```

#### Exit Animation
- Fades out over 200ms
- Removed from DOM after animation completes
- Other toasts smoothly transition up due to `space-y-2`

---

### 13.10 Accessibility

#### WCAG Compliance
- **Contrast**: All colors meet WCAG 2.2 AA
  - Success: Green-800 on Green-50 = 5.2:1
  - Error: Red-800 on Red-50 = 5.4:1
  - Warning: Yellow-800 on Yellow-50 = 4.9:1
  - Info: Blue-800 on Blue-50 = 5.1:1

#### Screen Reader Support
```tsx
// Toast is announced to screen readers
<div role="alert" aria-live="assertive">
  <p className="text-sm font-medium">{title}</p>
  {message && <p className="mt-1 text-sm">{message}</p>}
</div>

// Close button has label
<button
  className="..."
  onClick={() => onClose(id)}
  aria-label="Close notification"
>
  <X className="h-5 w-5" />
</button>
```

#### Keyboard Navigation
- **Close Button**: Focusable and keyboard accessible
- **Tab Order**: Natural tab order (title → message → close button)
- **Enter/Space**: Activates close button

---

### 13.11 Anti-Patterns

❌ **Too Many Toasts at Once**
```tsx
// WRONG: Overwhelming user
for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
  toast.show({ type: 'info', title: `Message ${i}` });
}

// CORRECT: Show one summary toast
toast.show({
  type: 'success',
  title: '10 items processed',
  message: 'View details in the activity log.',
});
```

❌ **Using Toast for Persistent Errors**
```tsx
// WRONG: Toast disappears, user loses error info
toast.show({
  type: 'error',
  title: 'Form has 12 errors',
  message: 'Check all fields',
});

// CORRECT: Show inline errors on form
<TextField
  name="email"
  error={true}
  errorMessage="Invalid email address"
/>
```

❌ **Missing Context in Toast**
```tsx
// WRONG: User doesn't know what succeeded
toast.show({
  type: 'success',
  title: 'Success',
});

// CORRECT: Specific message
toast.show({
  type: 'success',
  title: 'Payment Successful',
  message: 'Transaction ID: TXN123456',
});
```

---
